<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=t_rah&buddyTimeStamp=20060227&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fload_buddy_xml.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193060402&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Terrah</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Terrah lives at <a href='/home/?user=t_rah'>26667 Clover Lane</a> on the windswept shores in Lakeview.  Regardless of the season, she's enjoyed her lakefront home ever since she moved to Millsberry on October 18, 2005.<br><br>Terrah is easy to spot around town because she's always on the move!  She has a very busy schedule, but instead of stressing her out, it fits in perfectly with her active lifestyle.  After classes let out for the day at <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a>, Terrah often heads straight for <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park">Peabody Park</a>.  During spring or summer, she's usually busy with soccer practice on most afternoons, but since the opening of the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/gamepages/flashgame_ctp.phtml?game_id=360">ice rink</a>, she's laced up her skates almost every day.  Whether she's just practicing or playing in a league game, Terrah loves to speed across the ice and score a breakaway goal. <br><br>You might expect someone as competitive as Terrah to be a little too intense, but she's really quite the opposite!  Terrah is actually very friendly, and she's also a great teammate.  In fact, she often treats her fellow players to ice cream or pizza after a game, whether they've won or lost.  Terrah believes that being able to work as a team is a victory in itself.   If you're ever at a pizza parlor and see a girl wearing light blue, pink, and orange whos surrounded by a group of friends, it's probably Terrah!<br><br>Terrah credits her love of music and singing as being a key reason for her friendliness.  She says that performing for an audience has made her a more open and easygoing person.  Plus, Terrah often meets new friends while browsing through the CD racks of her favorite music store, searching for the latest pop, jazz, and disco releases.  In fact, Terrah first met her best friend when both of them were singing along to a song that was being played on the stereo at a nearby music store.  Terrah recently paid a visit to the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a> to try her hand at making some music of her own.  Her enthusiasm obviously paid off, because one of her songs has jumped to the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Terrah, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!<br></div>
